CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 21, 1967, pg. 16 reads: "Mr. and Mrs. Vernard McKenny" Portion of accompanying article reads: "Robinson -McKenny Rites Held at Central Baptist - One of the season's most fashionable weddings took place recently at Central Baptist Church when Miss Betty Robinson became the bride of Vernard McKenny."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of groom Vernard McKenny and bride Betty Robinson wearing light colored boat neck dress and veil, walking down aisle in Central Baptist Church
